## ðŸ›¡ï¸ 1ï¸âƒ£ ANTIVIRUS vs EDR vs MDR vs XDR (REAL SOC VIEW)

### ðŸ”¹ WHAT THEY ARE

| Technology     | What It Actually Does            | SOC Reality                     |
| -------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Antivirus (AV) | Signature + basic heuristics     | Stops known malware only        |
| EDR            | Behavioral telemetry + response  | Primary investigation tool      |
| MDR            | EDR + human monitoring           | Outsourced detection & response |
| XDR            | Correlates endpoint + other logs | Detection enrichment layer      |

### ðŸ”¹ WHY SOC CARES

Misunderstanding leads to:

* Assuming protection exists when it doesnâ€™t
* Ignoring highâ€‘value alerts

---

## ðŸš¦ 2ï¸âƒ£ DETECTION vs PREVENTION

### ðŸ”¹ DETECTION

Identifies suspicious or malicious behavior

Examples

* Encoded PowerShell
* LSASS access attempt

### ðŸ”¹ PREVENTION

Stops execution or blocks behavior

Examples

* Malware execution blocked
* Script terminated

### ðŸ”¹ SOC RULE

> A blocked attack is still an **attack attempt**

Detection without prevention = visibility
Prevention without detection = blind confidence

---

## ðŸ”’ 3ï¸âƒ£ QUARANTINE vs CONTAINMENT vs ISOLATION

### ðŸ”¹ QUARANTINE (FILE LEVEL)

* Removes file access
* File moved to secure location

### ðŸ”¹ CONTAINMENT (PROCESS / BEHAVIOR)

* Stops execution or persistence
* Limits attacker actions

### ðŸ”¹ ISOLATION (NETWORK LEVEL)

* Endpoint cut off from network
* Used during active compromise

### ðŸ”¹ WHEN TO ISOLATE

* Credential theft detected
* Lateral movement observed

---

## ðŸ§¨ 4ï¸âƒ£ ENDPOINT ATTACK TECHNIQUES (DEFENSIVE VIEW)

| Technique          | What Attacker Does | SOC Signal         |
| ------------------ | ------------------ | ------------------ |
| Initial execution  | User runs payload  | Office â†’ shell     |
| LOLBins abuse      | Native tools       | powershell.exe     |
| Credential dumping | Steal creds        | LSASS access       |
| Persistence        | Maintain access    | Startup / registry |
| Lateral movement   | Move internally    | PsExec / RDP       |

